Job Description:
* Operate the day-to-day sales operations;
* Maintain and develop relationships with customer;
* Introduce and assist customer for products available;
* Greet customers with a customer service standard trained by the company;
* Aim to achieve monthly or annual targets;
* Provide consultation to the customers, customer orientation, and other assigned tasks from direct supervisor/manager.

Job Requirement:
* Skills and Qualifications:

- Good knowledge of the operation, repair, and safety of biomedical equipment and instruments.
- Good knowledge of the operational aspects and environment of biomedical equipment as it relates to the treatment of patients;
- Working knowledge of international safety codes and manufacturer specifications;
- Ability to determine the cause of operational malfunction of biomedical equipment and make necessary repairs;
- Inspects medical equipment to ensure compliance with manufacturers specifications and code requirements;
- Calibrates equipment to ensure accuracy and correct operation;
- Documents repairs, calibrations, periodic safety inspections and preventive maintenance for maintaining database on departmental activities;
- Ability to communicate and work well with others;
- Ability to carry out instructions;
- Ability to use computer applications such as spreadsheets, word processing, calendar, e-mail in performing work assignments ;
- Ability to read, write, speak, understand and communicate in English sufficiently to perform the essential duties of the position;

* Salary: Attractive package and bonus. 
If you are interested to join our team of energetic and enterprising medical professionals in a diverse environment, please email your resume to careers@tph.asia. For further information, you can contact HR Department via mail above and by phone 012388836 (Telegram). 
Hospital address: #16&18, Street 21, Sangkat Tonlé Bassac, Khan Chamkarmon, Phnom Penh

